The paper presents a novel approach for designing optimal architectures for deep neural networks, which is a common topic in the machine learning community. The use of heterogeneous sensitivity in the nodes of the network suggests a focus on optimization and regularization techniques, which are often discussed in the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The specific applications mentioned in the paper, such as object recognition, facial expression recognition, and object detection, are all related to computer vision, which is a sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The use of neural networks also suggests a focus on the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper's approach to minimizing computational complexity is also relevant to the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
